      "memo": "Exhaust arbitrage typically involves no export control issues because interaction data is commercially generated rather than derived from controlled technology.",
      "detail": "No control exposure means exhaust data falls outside export control regimes because it is commercially generated interaction data. The absence of control obligations simplifies internal arbitrage by removing regulatory friction on data movement. No control issue keeps the stance focused on the commercial economics of exhaust rather than regulatory compliance. The uncontrolled character contributes to the frictionless accumulation that makes arbitrage possible."
    },
